TopicDetails.title: ERC PROOF OF CONCEPT GRANTS1
TopicDetails.callTitle: Call for proposals for ERC Proof of Concept Grant1

types.typeOfAction: HORIZON-ERC-POC HORIZON ERC Proof of Concept Grants

3317412.action: ERC-2022-POC1 - HORIZON-ERC-POC HORIZON ERC Proof of Concept Grants

TopicDetails.description:
Objective:

Objectives:

The ERC Proof of Concept Grants aim to facilitate exploration of the commercial and social innovation potential of ERC funded research and are therefore available only to Principal Investigators whose proposals draw substantially on their ERC funded research.

Size of ERC Proof of Concept Grants:

The financial contribution will be awarded as a lump sum of EUR 150 000 for a period of 18 months. The ERC expects that normally proof of concept activities should be completed within 12 months. However, to allow for those projects that require more preparation time, the grant agreements will be signed for 18 months. Extensions of the duration of proof of concept projects may be granted only exceptionally.
The lump sum will cover the beneficiaries' direct and indirect eligible costs for the project: if the project is implemented properly the amounts will be paid regardless of the costs actually incurred. The lump sum has been designed to cover the beneficiaries’ personnel costs, subcontracting, purchase costs, others cost categories and indirect costs.

Profile of the ERC Proof of Concept Eligible Principal Investigator:

All Principal Investigators in one of the main grants are eligible to participate and apply for an ERC Proof of Concept Grant. Principal Investigators in an ongoing main grant are eligible to apply to both Proof of Concept calls. Principal Investigators in a main grant that has ended less than 12 months before 1 January 2021 are eligible to apply only to call ERC-2022-PoC1. Principal Investigators in a main grant that has ended less than 12 months before 1 January 2022 are eligible to apply to both calls ERC-2022-PoC1 and ERC-2022-PoC2.

Principal Investigators may submit only one proposal under each Work Programme 2022 Proof of Concept call. If further submissions are made at different cut-off dates under call ERC-2022-PoC2, only the first admissible and eligible proposal will be considered.

Synergy Grant Principal Investigators are eligible to apply only with the written consent of all Principal Investigators in the same Synergy Grant project.

For further information please see the ERC Work Programme 2022.

<p><strong> <span style="font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: medium;">1. Adm</span></strong><span style="font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: medium;"><strong>issibility and Eligibility Conditions:</strong> </span>The conditions specific to ERC grants are described in the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022</a><b> </b>under the heading <span lang="EN-IE">'Admissibility and eligibility criteria' and in the </span><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/guidance/erc-rules-for-submission-and-evaluation_he-erc_en.pdf" target="_blank"><span lang="EN-GB">ERC Rules of Submission</span></a>. An overview is provided below:</p>
<p><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Admissible and eligible proposals:</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB"> </span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">All proposals must be complete, readable, accessible and be submitted before the relevant deadline. Incomplete proposals may be declared inadmissible (see ERC Proof of Concept Grant proposal submission and description below).<br />
</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">The content of the proposal must relate to the objectives and to the grant type set out in the call, as defined in this work programme.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif"> </span></span>If a proposal is considered not to relate to the objectives of the grant and/or call for proposals, it will be declared ineligible.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes"> </span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">A proposal will only be deemed ineligible on grounds of ‘scope’ in clear-cut cases. </span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">Where there is a doubt on the admissibility or eligibility of a proposal, the evaluation may proceed pending a decision following an admissibility and eligibility review committee. If it becomes clear before, during or after the evaluation phase, that one or more of the admissibility or eligibility criteria have not been met, the proposal will be declared inadmissible or ineligible and it will be rejected.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"> <br />
</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">A maximum of three Proof of Concept Grants may be awarded per main grant project, except for Synergy Grant, in which case a maximum of six Proof of Concept Grants may be awarded per ERC funded project.</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
line-height:normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><br />
<b>Eligible Principal Investigator:</b> </span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">All Principal Investigators in one of the main grants are eligible to participate and apply for an ERC Proof of Concept Grant. Principal Investigators in a </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">main grant that has ended less than 12 months before 1 January 2021 are eligible to apply only to call <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">ERC-2022-PoC1</b>. Principal Investigators in a main grant that is ongoing or has ended less than 12 months before 1 January 2022 are eligible to apply to both calls <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">ERC-2022-PoC1</b> and<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"> ERC-2022-PoC2</b> (second call under the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf" target="_blank">ERC Work Programme 2022</a>, to be published on 16/11/2021).</span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Synergy Grant Principal Investigators are eligible to apply only with the written consent of all Principal Investigators in the same Synergy Grant project.<br />
Principal Investigators may submit only one proposal under each <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color:blue">Work Programme 2022</span></a> Proof of Concept call. If further submissions are made at different cut-off dates under call ERC-2022-PoC2, only the first admissible and eligible proposal will be considered. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
line-height:normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">A  Principal Investigator whose proposal was rejected on the grounds of a  breach of research integrity in the calls for proposals under Work  Programmes 2019 or 2020 may not submit a proposal to the ERC-2022-PoC1  call. </span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">A  Principal Investigator whose proposal was rejected on the grounds of a  breach of research integrity in the calls for proposals under Work  Programmes 2020 or 2021 may not submit a proposal to the ERC-2022-PoC2  call.<br />
<br />
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
line-height:normal"><strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Eligible Host Institution</span></strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">:<br />
The Host Institution (Applicant Legal Entity) must engage the Principal Investigator for at least the duration of the proof of concept grant and must be established in a Member state or an Associated Country as a legal entity created under national law. It may also be an international organisation with headquarters in a Member State or associated country. Any type of legal entity, public or private, including universities, research organisations as well as undertakings can host the Principal Investigator and their team (see Annex 3 of the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf" target="_blank">ERC Work Programme 2022</a>).</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
line-height:normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">To be eligible for calls with deadlines in calendar year 2022, legal entities from a Member State or Associated Country that are public bodies, research organisations or higher education institutions (including private research organisations and private higher education institutions) must have a gender equality plan or an equivalent strategic document in place for the duration of the project. The gender equality plan or equivalent must fulfill the mandatory requirements listed in Annex 5 of the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf" target="_blank">ERC Work Programme 2022</a>.<br />
</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">  </span></p>

<p><b><br />
</b><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:red;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;">Proposal submission and description:<br />
</span></b></span></span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:red;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;">An <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/guidance/information-for-applicants_he-erc-poc_en.pdf" target="_blank">Information for Applicants</a> guidance is published on the ERC webiste and on the EU Funding & tenders opportunities Portal: it describes in detail how the submission forms should be completed. <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/support/faq;type=1;categories=p_submission_eval;programme=43108390;keyword=ERC-2022-POC1;period=null;status=0;sortQuery=publicationDate;faqListKey=faqSearchTablePageState" target="_blank">FAQs </a>(Frequently Asked Questions) are also available.</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:red;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"> <br />
</span>ATTENTION: use the new Part A and Part B forms specific to the ERC PoC Lump Sum call under Horizon Europe -  please download the latest version at the submission link below.</span><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><br />
</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">A complete PoC proposal is composed of:</span><br />
<b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">• Administrative Part A form</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">, including the Ethics Review Table (available in section 4): is an electronic form, available at step 5 of the submission process, once the draft proposal is created through the submission link below.<br />
(NB: To access the submission tool, you need first to register to the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/home" target="_blank"><span style="color:blue">Funding & tender opportunities Participant Portal</span></a>.)<br />
<br />
• <b>Proposal Part B form</b><u> and annexes</u>: download the two templates available from the submission link below (at step 5, after creation of draft proposal), fill in, upload in PDF format only and submit it via the submission tool. <br />
 <b>- Part B (Proposal description</b>): will provide detailed descriptions of the PoC project, its objectives, planning, execution, and required resources.<br />
    It will comprise the following required elements:<br />
      - The idea and justification of the breakthrough innovation potential: max. 3 pages<br />
      - The approach and methodology to explore the innovation potential: max. 6 pages <br />
      - The capacity and commitment of the Principal Investigator: max. 1 page.<br />
- <b>Host Institution Binding Statement of Support</b> <b>Letter</b> (NB: For Principal Investigators in a Synergy grant, only the host institution of the Principal Investigator applying to the PoC call must confirm its association with and its support to the project and the Principal Investigator.)<br />
<b>- </b>If applicable, an <b>Ethics review self-assessment</b> (with documentation related to ethics or security issues) </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;

<p> </p>
<p><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:
107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB" lang="EN-US">2. Eligible countries:</span></b></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">The conditions specific to the ERC are described in the <span class="field-content"><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022 </a></span>under the heading Admissibility and Eligibility criteria and in Annex 3. An overview is provided below:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">The ERC actions are open to <b>researchers of any nationality</b> who intend to conduct their research activity in any Member State or Associated Country. <b>Principal Investigators</b> may be of <b>any age and nationality</b> and may reside in any country in the world at the time of the application.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">A number of non-EU/non-Associated Countries that are not automatically eligible for funding have made specific provisions for making funding available for their participants in Horizon Europe projects. See the information in the </span><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/guidance/programme-guide_horizon_en.pdf">Horizon Europe Programme Guide</a></span></u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">.</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Operational capacity</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">: As indicated in the </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-IE" lang="EN-IE"><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022</a>, page 6, footnote 3: </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Applicants whose proposals are recommended for funding are deemed to fulfil the operational capacity requirements of Article 198(3) </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-IE" lang="EN-IE">of Regulation (EU, Euratom) </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2018/1046 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 18 July 2018 on the financial rules applicable to the general budget of the Union, amending Regulations (EU) No 1296/2013, (EU) No 1301/2013, (EU) No 1303/2013, (EU) No 1304/2013, (EU) No 1309/2013, (EU) No 1316/2013, (EU) No 223/2014, (EU) No 283/2014, and Decision No 541/2014/EU and repealing Regulation (EC, Euratom) No 966/2012 (OJ L 193, 30.07.2018, p. 1) </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:
107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-IE" lang="EN-IE">(the 'Financial Regulation').</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Security:</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"> Please refer to the</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;background:#C6DBEF;mso-ansi-language:EN-IE" lang="EN-IE"> <span class="MsoHyperlink"><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf"><span style="color:#2897B7">ERC Work Programme 2022</span></a></span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-IE" lang="EN-IE">, Annex 4.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">Exclusion</span></b><span style="font-size:
12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US" lang="EN-US">: Please refer to </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022 </a>under the heading Admissibility and Eligibility criteria and </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">in </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">the final page of this work programme:</span><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">Applicants that are subject to the administrative sanction of exclusion or are in one of the exclusion situations set out by the Financial Regulation are banned from receiving EU grants and can NOT participate. See articles 136 and 141 of the Financial Regulation, as well as important information on possible exclusion and registration of economic operators in the Commission’s Early Detection and Exclusion System (EDES). </span></p>

"Times New Roman",serif">The conditions specific to ERC are described in the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022</a> under the heading "Evaluation criteria" and "Evaluation outcome", as well as in the </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif"><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/guidance/erc-rules-for-submission-and-evaluation_he-erc_en.pdf " target="_blank">ERC Rules for Submission and Evaluation</a>. </span></span>An overview is provided below:</span></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">Evaluation criteria</span></strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">Proof of Concept Grants are awarded in relation to an ERC-funded project under one of the main grants. The evaluation of admissible and eligible proposals will look into ideas stemming from ERC-funded projects and will select among them the most competitive for further development towards an innovation. </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">The activities to be funded will draw substantially on the ERC-funded research under the main frontier research grant.</span></span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">For ERC Proof of Concept grants, excellence is the sole criterion of evaluation. It will be applied in conjunction to the evaluation of both: the breakthrough innovation potential, approach and methodology of the project; and the capacity and commitment of the Principal Investigator. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">The detailed evaluation elements applying to the excellence of the project and the Principal Investigator are set out in the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf">ERC Work Programme 2022</a>.</span></p>

<p><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Evaluation process:</span></b><br />
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Experts will evaluate independently </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">each admissible and eligible proposal </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">in a single-step process, </span></span>and mark it as "very good", "good" or "fail" for each of the three evaluation elements.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">In order to be considered for funding, proposals will have to be awarded a pass mark (“very good” or “good”) by a majority of experts on each of the evaluation elements. A proposal which fails one or more of the elements will not be ranked and will not be funded.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">If there is not enough budget to fund all the proposals which pass all three evaluation elements, those proposals which pass all three evaluation elements will be ranked according to the marks which they received from experts sorted by the order in which the evaluation elements appear above. Proposals will be funded in order of this ranking.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">If necessary, experts will meet as an evaluation panel in order to determine a priority order for proposals which have the same ranking.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:
AR-SA"><br />
</span><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>

<span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif">The financial contribution will be awarded as a lump sum of <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">EUR 150 000</b> for a period of <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">18 months</b>. The ERC expects that normally proof of concept activities should be completed within 12 months. However, to allow for those projects that require more preparation time, the grant agreements will be signed for 18 months. Extensions of the duration of proof of concept projects may be granted only exceptionally.</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:
107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">6.</span></b><span style="font-size:
12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"><strong> Open Science</strong></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Open science is a core principle of the ERC. The ERC is committed to the principle of open access to the published output of research, including in particular peer-reviewed articles and monographs. It also supports the basic principle of open access to research data and data related products such as computer code. The ERC considers that providing free online access to all these materials can be the most effective way of ensuring that the fruits of the research it funds can be accessed, read and used as the basis for further research.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">Under Horizon Europe, beneficiaries of ERC grants must ensure open access to all peer-reviewed scientific publications relating to their results as set out in the <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/common/agr-contr/general-mga_horizon-euratom_en.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color:windowtext;text-decoration:none;text-underline:
none">Model Grant Agreement used for ERC actions</span></a>. Beneficiaries must ensure that they or the authors retain sufficient intellectual property rights to comply with their open access requirements.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">In addition, beneficiaries of ERC grants funded under the </span><a href="https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/wp-call/2022/wp_horizon-erc-2022_en.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:blue;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">ERC Work Programme 2022</span></a><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif"> will be covered by the provisions on research data management as set out in the Model Grant Agreement used for ERC actions. In particular, whenever a project generates research data, beneficiaries are required to manage it in line with the principles of findability, accessibility, interoperability, and reusability as described by the FAIR principles initiative, and establish a data management plan within the first six months of project implementation. Open access to research data should be ensured under the principle ‘as open as possible, as closed as necessary’. These provisions are designed to facilitate access, re-use and preservation of the research data generated during the ERC funded research work.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US"> <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

TopicDetails.supportInfo:
ERC PoC Applicants Mailbox - for queries related to the Proof of Concept Calls.

ERC 2022 PoC Call Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs): F&T Portal - ERC webiste

Funding & Tenders Portal FAQ – find the answers to most frequently asked questions on submission of proposals, evaluation and grant management.

Online Manual is your guide on the procedures from proposal submission to managing your grant.

IT HOW TO  wiki site provides an online IT manual with screenshots.

ERC National Contat Points (NCP) - Contact your ERC NCP for further assistance in your national language(s).

Research Enquiry Service – ask questions about any aspect of European research in general and the EU Research Framework Programmes in particular.

IT Helpdesk – contact the Funding & Tenders Portal IT helpdesk for questions such as forgotten passwords, access rights and roles, technical aspects of submission of proposals, etc.

Ethics - for compliance with ethical issues, see the Online Manual.

European IPR Helpdesk assists you on intellectual property issues.

The European Charter for Researchers and the Code of Conduct for their recruitment - consult the general principles and requirements specifying the roles, responsibilities and entitlements of researchers, employers and funders of researchers.

Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union

European Convention on Human Rights
TopicDetails.sepTemplate:
To access the Electronic Submission Service, please click on the submission-button next to the type of action and the type of model grant agreement that corresponds to your proposal. You will then be asked to confirm your choice, as it cannot be changed in the submission system. Upon confirmation, you will be linked to the correct entry point.

To access existing draft proposals for this topic, please login to the Funding & Tenders Portal and select the My Proposals page of the My Area section.

latestInfos.content:
PRESS RELEASE on EVALUATION RESULTS of the ERC Proof of Concept Lump Sum Grant 2022-1:

- Proof of Concept Highlighted Projects

- €25 million to Edge Frontier Research closer to Market

- List of ERC PoC Grantees

EVALUATION RESULTS of the ERC Proof of Concept Lump Sum Grant 2022-1:

Call for proposals: ERC-2022-PoC1 - ERC PROOF OF CONCEPT GRANT
Published: 15 July 2021
Single Deadline: 14 October 2021 at 17:00 (Brussels local time)
Available Budget: 25.000.000 €

The ERCEA, assisted by independent experts, has completed the evaluation of proposals submitted to the above call. The names of the experts that evaluated Horizon Europe proposals are published, collectively for each part of Horizon Europe and once per year, on the FUNDING & TENDERS PORTAL .

The results of the evaluation are as follows:
Number of submitted proposals: 351
Number of inadmissible proposals: 0
Number of ineligible proposals: 3
Number of withdrawn proposals: 0
Number of above-threshold proposals [1]: 316
Number of proposals retained for funding [1]: 166
Total budget requested for proposals retained for funding: 24.900.000 €

We informed the applicants about the evaluation results for their proposals on 1 February 2022.

[1] The number of proposals that can finally be funded depends on the final available budget and the completion of the formal procedures needed to conclude grant agreements.

The first grant agreements are expected to be signed in February-March 2022.

Information on the selected projects will be published on CORDIS after signature of the grant agreements.

For questions, please contact the Research Enquiry Service.

ERC Proof of Concept Call Coordination

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:36.0pt"><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">Dear Applicants,</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:36.0pt"><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">The final results for the first Proof of Concept evaluation round of Horizon Europe (ERC-2022-PoC1 call) have been published on the F&T Portal this 1st February.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:36.0pt"><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">Best regards,</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:36.0pt"><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US" lang="EN-US">ERC PoC Call coordination team</span></p>

Dear Applicants,

Due to technical difficulties, the communication of the evaluation results for this call (planned to be released in January) is delayed. 

Our IT teams are working to resolve the issue.

We apologise for any inconvenience this may cause,

the ERC Proof of Concept Grant Call Coordination Team

The ERC-2022-PoC1 call is closed.
A total of 351 proposals were submitted in response to the single deadline (14 October 2021) of the first of the 2022 ERC Proof of Concept Lump Sum Call ERC-2022-PoC1. This represents a 34% decrease compared to the overall number of proposals submitted for the ERC 2020 PoC call evaluations (3 deadlines). However, at the same time this is the highest number ever received to an ERC PoC deadline.

The dates for ERC-2022-PoC2, the second call under the ERC Work Programme 2022, have been published on the ERC website: opening for submission on the Participant Portal on 16th November 2021, with 3 cut-off dates (deadlines): 15 February 2022 - 19 May 2022 and 29 September 2022 (17:00:00 time zone Brussels time).
The submission session is now available for: ERC-2022-POC1(HORIZON-ERC-POC)
